From: Batocera Linux Team <batocera@batocera.linux>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] fix: use inline asm movdir64b wrapper with GCC

GCC exposes _movdir64b as an always_inline intrinsic that requires the
translation unit to be compiled with -mmovdir64b. Xenia already gates use
of the movdir64b implementation through runtime CPU feature detection, so
avoid requiring the whole file to be built for that instruction by using
the same inline assembly wrapper on GCC that is already used on Clang.

Signed-off-by: Batocera Linux Team <batocera@batocera.linux>
---
 src/xenia/base/memory.cc | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/xenia/base/memory.cc b/src/xenia/base/memory.cc
--- a/src/xenia/base/memory.cc
+++ b/src/xenia/base/memory.cc
@@ -35,7 +35,7 @@ using xe::swcache::CacheLine;
 #if XE_ARCH_AMD64
 static constexpr unsigned NUM_CACHELINES_IN_PAGE = 4096 / sizeof(CacheLine);
 
-#if defined(__clang__)
+#if defined(__clang__) || defined(__GNUC__)
 XE_FORCEINLINE
 static void mvdir64b(void* to, const void* from) {
   __asm__("movdir64b %1, %0" : : "r"(to), "m"(*(char*)from) : "memory");
